    "body": "I also thought it might be a Warp bug, but it behaves similarly in iTerm:\n\n<img width=\"346\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d2426c01-488f-4648-b558-fb36d29d4b27\" />\n\nI don't know what you mean when you ask if prompts and output use the same font, and I don't know how I can determine what font the output is trying to use.\n\nI also don't know how to check my nerd font version, although I just downloaded it using the starship home page link. When I ask Emacs about the git \"branch\" symbol, it reports\n```\n    position: 410 of 1058 (39%), column: 12\n    character:  (displayed as ) (codepoint 62488, #o172030, #xf418)\n    charset: unicode (Unicode (ISO10646))\n    code point in charset: 0xF418\n    syntax: w \twhich means: word\n    category: L:Strong L2R\n    to input: type \"C-x 8 RET f418\"\n    buffer code: #xEF #x90 #x98\n    file code: #xEF #x90 #x98 (encoded by coding system utf-8-unix)\n    display: by this font (glyph code):\n    mac-ct:-*-DroidSansMono Nerd Font Mono-regular-normal-normal-*-14-*-*-*-m-0-iso10646-1 (#x810)\n```",
